{"title_page": "CoinDesk", "text_new": "{{short description|News site about bitcoin and digital currencies, owned by Digital Currency Group}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name             = CoinDesk\n| logo             = Coindesk-logo.png\n| location         = New York, NY\n| launch_date      = {{start date and age|2013|05}}\n| url              = {{URL|https://www.coindesk.com/|coindesk.com}}\n| country          = U.S.\n| founder          = Shakil Khan\n| editor           = Marc Hochstein\n| area_served      = Worldwide\n| industry         = Digital Currency\n| employees        = 15+\n| international    = yes\n}}\n\n'''CoinDesk''' is a news site specializing in [[bitcoin]] and [[digital currencies]]. The site was founded by Shakil Khan and was subsequently acquired by [[Digital Currency Group]].\n\n==History==\nCoinDesk began publishing in May 2013, and was founded by serial entrepreneur Shakil Khan.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cutler|first1=Kim-Mai|title=Angel Investor, Spotify Fixer Shakil Khan Launches Coindesk, A Bitcoin Resource|url=https://techcrunch.com/2013/05/01/coindesk/|publisher=TechCrunch|date=May 1, 2013}}</ref> Khan is also an investor in [[BitPay]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Olanoff|first1=Drew|title=BitPay Banks $510K In Investment To Become PayPal for Bitcoin, Already Has 2,100 Businesses On Board|url=https://techcrunch.com/2013/01/07/bitpay-banks-500k-in-angel-investment-to-become-paypal-for-bitcoin-already-has-2100-businesses-on-board/|publisher=TechCrunch|date=Jan 7, 2013}}</ref> a bitcoin payment processor. In September 2013, Jon Matonis, former executive director of the [[Bitcoin Foundation]], joined CoinDesk as a contributing editor.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bradbury|first1=Danny|title=Jon Matonis joins the CoinDesk team|url=https://www.coindesk.com/jon-matonis-joins-the-coindesk-team/|publisher=CoinDesk|date=September 9, 2013}}</ref> CoinDesk also provides guides to bitcoin for those new to digital currencies.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Summers|first1=Nick|title=Baffled by the world of Bitcoin? This beginner\u2019s guide will tell you everything you need to know|url=https://thenextweb.com/insider/2013/08/21/baffled-by-the-world-of-bitcoin-this-beginners-guide-will-tell-you-everything-you-need-to-know/|publisher=The Next Web|date=August 21, 2013}}</ref> In January 2016, CoinDesk was acquired by [[Digital Currency Group]] for an estimated amount of US$500K-600K.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Matney|first1=Lucas|title=CoinDesk Gets Acquired By Digital Currency Group|url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/01/13/coindesk-acquired-by-digital-currency-group/|accessdate=26 April 2018|work=TechCrunch|date=13 January 2016}}</ref> In January 2017, the company acquired Lawnmower, a blockchain data and research platform.<ref>{{cite web|author=Roberts, Daniel |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/the-biggest-bitcoin-news-site-bought-the-best-bitcoin-data-app-165456815.html |title=The biggest bitcoin news site bought the best bitcoin data app |publisher=Yahoo! Finance |date=January 30, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Bitcoin Price Index==\nThe CoinDesk Bitcoin Price Index (CoinDesk BPI) was launched in September 2013.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Del Rey|first1=Jason|title=What\u2019s a Bitcoin Really Worth? CoinDesk Thinks It Has the Answer.|url=http://allthingsd.com/20130911/whats-a-bitcoin-really-worth-coindesk-thinks-it-has-the-answer/|publisher=All Things D|date=September 11, 2013}}</ref> The Bitcoin Price Index is an average of bitcoin prices across bitcoin exchanges, and began by using price data from [[Bitstamp]], [[BTC-e]] and CampBX. Although [[Mt. Gox]] data was not used initially, due to withdrawal concerns for US customers,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Matonis|first1=Jon|title=CoinDesk launches proprietary Bitcoin Price Index|url=https://www.coindesk.com/coindesk-launches-proprietary-bitcoin-price-index/|publisher=CoinDesk|date=September 11, 2013}}</ref> in November 2013, Mt. Gox was added to the BPI due to \"a reduction in the risk premium and the option of additional deposit/withdrawal methods\".<ref>{{cite web|title=About the Bitcoin Price Index|url=https://www.coindesk.com/price/bitcoin-price-index/|website=CoinDesk|publisher=CoinDesk}}</ref> The [[Mt. Gox]] bitcoin exchange was eventually removed from the index in February 2014 after its \"persistent failure to meet the index's standards for inclusion\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Forgione|first1=Sam|title=Bitcoin plunges after marketplace indefinitely halts withdrawals|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/11/us-investing-bitcoin-idUSBREA191Y220140211|agency=Reuters|publisher=Reuters|date=Feb 11, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe index was restored to an average of three exchanges in March 2014 with the inclusion of [[Bitfinex]] price data, according to CoinDesk: \"Since the decline of Mt. Gox, we have observed that Bitfinex has been able to sustain a dramatic increase in its share of the total volume of U.S. dollar-denominated bitcoins traded\".<ref name=wsj20140312>\n{{cite news |last1=Casey|first1=Michael J. |last2=Vigna|first2=Paul |title=BitBeat: Coindesk Index Finds a Mt. Gox Replacement |url=https://blogs.wsj.com/moneybeat/2014/03/12/bitbeat-coindesk-index-finds-a-mt-gox-replacement/ |work=[[Wall Street Journal]] |date=Mar 12, 2014 }}</ref>{{update after|2016|8|9}}<!-- needs update since the Bitfinex exchange is down as of the first week of August 2016, due to a hack.  What is the CoinDesk index now??? -->\n\nPublications which have referenced the Bitcoin Price Index data or price include the BBC,<ref>{{cite news|title=Bitcoin price falls to 11-month low|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-29507443|publisher=BBC|date=Oct 6, 2014}}</ref> WSJ,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Vigna|first1=Paul|last2=J. Casey|first2=Michael|title=BitBeat: More Pain For Bitcoin Prices; Are Chinese Miners To Blame?|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/moneybeat/2014/09/19/bitbeat-more-pain-for-bitcoin-prices-are-chinese-miners-to-blame/|publisher=Wall Street Journal|date=Sep 19, 2014}}</ref> Reuters,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Forgione|first1=Sam|title=Bitcoin plunges after marketplace indefinitely halts withdrawals|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/11/us-investing-bitcoin-idUSBREA191Y220140211|agency=Reuters|publisher=Reuters|date=Feb 11, 2014}}</ref> NY Times,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ember|first1=Sydney|title=Single Winner of All Bitcoins in U.S. Auction|url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/07/01/single-winner-of-all-bitcoins-in-u-s-auction/|publisher=New York Times|date=July 1, 2014}}</ref> CNBC<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rosenfield|first1=Everett|title=Bitcoin gets bit by a summertime swoon|url=https://www.cnbc.com/id/101916834|publisher=CNBC|date=Aug 13, 2014}}</ref> and Bloomberg.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dougherty|first1=Carter|title=Bitcoin Price Plunges as Mt. Gox Exchange Halts Activity|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-02-07/bitcoin-price-falls-as-mt-gox-exchange-halts-activity.html|publisher=Bloomberg|date=Feb 7, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==State of Bitcoin report==\nIn February 2014, CoinDesk released its first 'State of Bitcoin' report. The aim of the report is \"to provide an overview of key cryptocurrency trends, challenges, and opportunities, while also highlighting the most important developments over the last year\u201d.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Del Rey|first1=Jason|title=(Almost) Everything You Want to Know About Bitcoin, in One Report|url=http://recode.net/2014/02/27/almost-everything-you-want-to-know-about-bitcoin-in-one-report/|publisher=Re/Code|date=Feb 27, 2014}}</ref> A follow-up report in Q2 2014 highlighted that venture capital investment in bitcoin companies was up 28 percent compared to the previous quarter,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Carson|first1=Biz|title=This week in bitcoin: VC investment is up and shows no signs of stopping after Xapo|url=https://gigaom.com/2014/07/11/this-week-in-bitcoin-vc-investment-is-up-and-shows-no-signs-of-stopping-after-xapo/|publisher=Gigaom|date=July 11, 2014}}</ref> and that VC investment was pouring into European Bitcoin startups.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wile|first1=Rob|title=Investors Are Plowing Into European Bitcoin Firms Faster Than Any Other Region In The World|url=http://www.businessinsider.com.au/europe-bitcoin-investment-surge-2014-7|publisher=Business Insider|date=July 11, 2014}}</ref>\n\n== iPhone App ==\nIn April 2014, CoinDesk released an iOS app.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Russell|first1=Jon|title=Keep up with Bitcoin news and get price alerts with CoinDesk\u2019s new iOS app|url=https://thenextweb.com/apps/2014/04/30/keep-up-with-bitcoin-news-and-get-price-alerts-with-coindesks-new-ios-app/|publisher=The Next Web|date=April 30, 2014}}</ref> The app includes news stories and editorials, as well as its 'Bitcoin Price Index'.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://cryptodesk.in]{{Official website|https://www.coindesk.com/}}\n\n{{Bitcoin}}\n{{Cryptocurrencies}}\n\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Cryptocurrencies]]\n[[Category:Bitcoin companies]]\n[[Category:Technology websites]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|News site about bitcoin and digital currencies, owned by Digital Currency Group}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name             = CoinDesk\n| logo             = Coindesk-logo.png\n| location         = New York, NY\n| launch_date      = {{start date and age|2013|05}}\n| url              = {{URL|https://www.coindesk.com/|coindesk.com}}\n| country          = U.S.\n| founder          = Shakil Khan\n| editor           = Marc Hochstein\n| area_served      = Worldwide\n| industry         = Digital Currency\n| employees        = 15+\n| international    = yes\n}}\n\n'''CoinDesk''' is a news site specializing in [[bitcoin]] and [[digital currencies]]. The site was founded by Shakil Khan and was subsequently acquired by [[Digital Currency Group]].\n\n==History==\nCoinDesk began publishing in May 2013, and was founded by serial entrepreneur Shakil Khan.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cutler|first1=Kim-Mai|title=Angel Investor, Spotify Fixer Shakil Khan Launches Coindesk, A Bitcoin Resource|url=https://techcrunch.com/2013/05/01/coindesk/|publisher=TechCrunch|date=May 1, 2013}}</ref> Khan is also an investor in [[BitPay]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Olanoff|first1=Drew|title=BitPay Banks $510K In Investment To Become PayPal for Bitcoin, Already Has 2,100 Businesses On Board|url=https://techcrunch.com/2013/01/07/bitpay-banks-500k-in-angel-investment-to-become-paypal-for-bitcoin-already-has-2100-businesses-on-board/|publisher=TechCrunch|date=Jan 7, 2013}}</ref> a bitcoin payment processor. In September 2013, Jon Matonis, former executive director of the [[Bitcoin Foundation]], joined CoinDesk as a contributing editor.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bradbury|first1=Danny|title=Jon Matonis joins the CoinDesk team|url=https://www.coindesk.com/jon-matonis-joins-the-coindesk-team/|publisher=CoinDesk|date=September 9, 2013}}</ref> CoinDesk also provides guides to bitcoin for those new to digital currencies.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Summers|first1=Nick|title=Baffled by the world of Bitcoin? This beginner\u2019s guide will tell you everything you need to know|url=https://thenextweb.com/insider/2013/08/21/baffled-by-the-world-of-bitcoin-this-beginners-guide-will-tell-you-everything-you-need-to-know/|publisher=The Next Web|date=August 21, 2013}}</ref> In January 2016, CoinDesk was acquired by [[Digital Currency Group]] for an estimated amount of US$500K-600K.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Matney|first1=Lucas|title=CoinDesk Gets Acquired By Digital Currency Group|url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/01/13/coindesk-acquired-by-digital-currency-group/|accessdate=26 April 2018|work=TechCrunch|date=13 January 2016}}</ref> In January 2017, the company acquired Lawnmower, a blockchain data and research platform.<ref>{{cite web|author=Roberts, Daniel |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/the-biggest-bitcoin-news-site-bought-the-best-bitcoin-data-app-165456815.html |title=The biggest bitcoin news site bought the best bitcoin data app |publisher=Yahoo! Finance |date=January 30, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Bitcoin Price Index==\nThe CoinDesk Bitcoin Price Index (CoinDesk BPI) was launched in September 2013.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Del Rey|first1=Jason|title=What\u2019s a Bitcoin Really Worth? CoinDesk Thinks It Has the Answer.|url=http://allthingsd.com/20130911/whats-a-bitcoin-really-worth-coindesk-thinks-it-has-the-answer/|publisher=All Things D|date=September 11, 2013}}</ref> The Bitcoin Price Index is an average of bitcoin prices across bitcoin exchanges, and began by using price data from [[Bitstamp]], [[BTC-e]] and CampBX. Although [[Mt. Gox]] data was not used initially, due to withdrawal concerns for US customers,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Matonis|first1=Jon|title=CoinDesk launches proprietary Bitcoin Price Index|url=https://www.coindesk.com/coindesk-launches-proprietary-bitcoin-price-index/|publisher=CoinDesk|date=September 11, 2013}}</ref> in November 2013, Mt. Gox was added to the BPI due to \"a reduction in the risk premium and the option of additional deposit/withdrawal methods\".<ref>{{cite web|title=About the Bitcoin Price Index|url=https://www.coindesk.com/price/bitcoin-price-index/|website=CoinDesk|publisher=CoinDesk}}</ref> The [[Mt. Gox]] bitcoin exchange was eventually removed from the index in February 2014 after its \"persistent failure to meet the index's standards for inclusion\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Forgione|first1=Sam|title=Bitcoin plunges after marketplace indefinitely halts withdrawals|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/11/us-investing-bitcoin-idUSBREA191Y220140211|agency=Reuters|publisher=Reuters|date=Feb 11, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe index was restored to an average of three exchanges in March 2014 with the inclusion of [[Bitfinex]] price data, according to CoinDesk: \"Since the decline of Mt. Gox, we have observed that Bitfinex has been able to sustain a dramatic increase in its share of the total volume of U.S. dollar-denominated bitcoins traded\".<ref name=wsj20140312>\n{{cite news |last1=Casey|first1=